                              TROUBLE SHOOTING

    If you should experience any problems with you Vidi-AMIGA 12, then
please try the following suggestions before taking the unit back to the
place of purchase or phoning the technical support line at ROMBO.

    Some people may find it all too easy to instantly blame the Vidi-AMIGA
12 if it appears not to function at first, but experience has taught us at
ROMBO that most problems are caused by the user simply not having read the
manual properly which can result in the product not being connected to the
Amiga correctly or being connected to the wrong type of video source.

                           PROBLEMS AND SOLUTIONS

              ERROR MESSAGE STATES - NO VIDEO SIGNAL DETECTED.

    Try connecting the video lead from the Amigas monochrome video out on
the rear of the computer to the video in on the Vidi-AMIGA 12.
    Now try grabbing an image if the no video message disappears then the
Vidi-AMIGA 12 is working and the fault lies with your original video source.
    Please refer to page 4 of the manual for details of the correct type of
video source to be used.

PAGE 44

                      BLACK AND WHITE VERTICAL STRIPES

    Please check that you have the Vidi-AMIGA 12 firmly connected to the
parallel port and if you have to use any extension leads from your parallel
port, please make sure they are also firmly seated.

    Please note that when using a parallel port extension cable that it must
be a short flat ribbon cable type and not a round cable. The reason for this
is that all 25 pins of the parallel port must be connected to the Vidi-AMIGA
12 in order for it to operate correctly.

    We also recommend that a extension lead no longer than 30cm be used. A
short extension cable is available from ROMBO. We can also supply a parallel
port switching box which works with the Vidi-AMIGA 12. We can not guarantee
that another companys will work.

                  IMAGE IS CORRUPTED WITH HORIZONTAL LINES

    This is usually caused by the Vidi-AMIGA 12's disk drive cable not been
connected.
    Please check that you have connected the drive lead to the external
drive port on your computer or the through port on any external drive that
you may have connected. As the Vidi-AMIGA 12 takes power through it.

PAGE 45

    Please note that some external drives do not have any form of through
port on them (or the power supply pins have not been wired up). This will
mean that you will have to purchase a drive port splitter which will allow
both an external drive and the Vidi-AMIGA 12 to be fitted simultaneously.

    A splitter device called TWIN IT may be available from a company called
George Thomson Services. Their phone number is (0707) 271117.

                    MONOCHROME INSTEAD OF COLOUR GRABBED

    This is usually caused by the user not setting their DISPLAY PREFS... to
a colour selection.

            COMPUTER ASKS FOR THE ORIGINAL DISK TO BE INSERTED.

    This is caused by the user making a backup disk which does not have the
same name as the original.
    Rename the backup disk to VidiAMIGA12 (no spaces!)

            ERROR MESSAGE - V34.Lib REQUIRED OR SIMILAR MESSAGE.

    This is usually caused by users booting up from hard drive or from their
Workbench disk. These users must use the INSTALL (or INSTALLWB1.3 for users
of Workbench 1.3) program supplied to copy the library files to either hard
drive or onto their Workbench disk.

